<td valign="bottom" colspan="2"><br>
<font class="head">About the Innovations Awards</font>
<hr noshade size="1"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2">

<table width="540" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
<tr><td width="390">



<!-- content starts here --> 
<font class="PromoOpsDateContact">Deadline: October 6, 2000</font><br><br>

<font class="body">

<i>Entry deadlines have passed, if you have questions about Innovations 2001 please call 
Cindy Hoag at 703 907 7629 or e-mail <a href="mailto:choag@ce.org">choag@ce.org</a>.</i><p>

<font class="subhead2">Show them what's on your mind!</font><br>
<br>
There is no higher honor than winning the Consumer Electronics Association's Innovations 2001 Design and Engineering Award. A panel of prominent industry
experts - your peers - will come together to select the most innovative products in every consumer electronics category. And, again this year, the prestigious Industrial Designers Society of America (IDSA) has endorsed and will advise Innovations 2001. Innovations 2001 is your chance to show the industry what¹s on your mind - and position yourself at the head of consumer technology.<br>
<br>
The Innovations 2001 awards program operates in conjunction with the 2001 International CES, annually drawing more than 3,600 domestic and international press, and more than 110,000 retailers, distributors and other consumer technology executives from around the world. They all want to see the Innovations winners - displayed only in the Innovations 2001 display area at the 2001 International CES, January 6-9, 2001, in Las Vegas, Nevada USA.<br>
<br> 
Innovations 2001 is all about the right exposure. Winning products will be placed under the spotlight. Winning companies will receive industry-wide recognition - and the right to attach the Innovations 2001 logo to all future packaging and advertising. This highly coveted logo separates your innovative product from the competition. In fact, Innovations 2001 winners receive numerous benefits; see below for a complete list:<br>
<br>
<br>
<a name="benefits"></a>
<font class="subhead">Benefits</font><br><br><ul>
<li>Inclusion in the prestigious Innovations 2001 display arena at the 2001 International CES show
<li>A beautiful Innovations 2001 award to display at CES or in your trophy case
<li>A listing in the Innovations 2001 online winners directory
<li>Inclusion in a CEA-issued press release
<li>Inclusion on the official website, www.CESweb.org </li><p></ul>
<a name="quals"></a>
<font class="subhead">Entry Qualifications</font><br><br>
To qualify to enter, you must be an exhibitor at the 2001 International CES; you must manufacture goods marketed in the United States; and your product entry must:<br>
<ul><li>Fit within the product category(ies) listed
<li>Have or will become available at retail outlets between January 1, 2000 and June 30, 2001<br>
<li>Be fully functional</ul><br><br>

<a name="deadlines"></a>
<font class="subhead">Deadlines and Fees</font><br><br>

<a name="dates"></a>
<font class="subhead2">Important Innovations 2001 Dates</font><br><br>
<table width="100%">
<tr><td><font class="body">Application Deadline</td><td><font class="body">Friday, October 6, 2000</td></tr>
<tr><td><font class="body">Extension Deadline</td><td><font class="body">Friday, October 13, 2000</td></tr>
<tr><td><font class="body">Innovations Judging</td><td><font class="body">November 1, 2000</td></tr>
<tr><td><font class="body">All Applicants Notified</td><td><font class="body">November 17, 2000</td></tr>
<tr><td><font class="body">Innovations Honorees Announced</td><td><font class="body">January 6, 2001 (Opening Day of the 2001 International CES)</td></tr>
</table><br>

<a name="fees"></a>
<font class="body">
<font class="subhead2">Fees (Cost per Entry)</font><br><br><ul>
<li>CEA member companies: $175 per entry
<li>Non-CEA member companies: $350 per entry
<li>Add $100 to the fees above if you submit your application in paper form only (non-electronically).</font><br><br>
</ul>
A one-week extension can be obtained for an additional processing fee of $300 per entry. Late applications will not be accepted without this processing fee. <br><br>

<a name="bos"></a>
<font class="subhead">Best of show award</font><br><br>
Now in its fourth year, the Innovations 2001 Best of Show award is given to the highest honored products in their category - for all categories with three or more entries. Best of Show honorees are highlighted throughout the Innovations 2001 promotional materials, and will be previewed in a special display in the Grand Lobby of the Las Vegas Convention Center during the 2001 International CES.<p>

